In a large skillet, brown sausage in oil over medium-high heat. Remove with a slotted spoon and keep warm. Add the vegetables, broth and soup mix to skillet. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10-12 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Return sausage to the pan. Combine cornstarch and cold water until smooth; stir into sausage mixture. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 1 minute or until thickened.